BigChainDB.CategoryDescription: With decentralized databases, it's much harder to maliciously change records because data is stored and verified in multiple locations, sometimes thousands of locations.  Hacks on these databases must control more than half of these validator nodes to take control of the network.  Transaction speeds also have the potential to be much quicker than with traditional data storage.
